    <h2>Whirlpool, North America's largest appliance family</h2>
    <p>Whirlpool Corporation operates the largest North American appliance brand family with substantial shared parts infrastructure across tiers. The brand hierarchy: JennAir (luxury, post-2020 Rise+Nord relaunch), KitchenAid (premium with cooking emphasis), Whirlpool (mainstream premium, this page), Maytag (mass-market heavy-duty), Amana (value), Roper (entry-tier, laundry-focused). Whirlpool mainstream premium sits in the middle of this hierarchy, above Maytag mass-market and Amana value but below KitchenAid and JennAir. Wall oven positioning at $800-2k.</p>
    <p>For LA service, Whirlpool Corporation's North American distribution network is among the strongest parts-supply channels in the US appliance-repair market. Common Whirlpool wall oven parts 1-3 day lead; specialty components 3-5 days. Shared parts commonality with Maytag + Amana siblings means parts-availability pool is effectively combined across the mid-tier family, bake elements, convection fan motors, and many sensor + control variants interchange between Whirlpool + Maytag + Amana comparable models.</p>
